def unified_strdate(date_str, day_first=True):
    import re
    import datetime
    if date_str is None:
        return None
    upload_date = None

    # Updated regular expression to match different date formats.
    if not re.match(r'^[\d]{1,2}[\-\.\s\/][\d]{1,2}[\-\.\s\/][\d]{4}$', date_str):
        date_str = re.sub(r' ?(\+|-)[\d]{2}:?[\d]{2}$', '', date_str)

        '%b %dnd %Y %I:%M%p',
        '%b %dth %Y %I:%M%p',
        '%Y %m %d',
        '%Y-%m-%d',
        '%Y/%m/%d',
        '%Y/%m/%d %H:%M:%S',
        '%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S',
        '%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S.%f',
        '%d.%m.%Y %H:%M',
        '%d.%m.%Y %H.%M',
        '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ',
        '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S.%fZ',
        '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S.%f0Z',
        '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S',
        '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S.%f',
        '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M',
    ]
    if day_first:
        format_expressions.extend([
            '%d-%m-%Y',
            '%d.%m.%Y',
            '%d/%m/%Y',
            '%d/%m/%y',
            '%d/%m/%Y %H:%M:%S',
        ])
    else:
        format_expressions.extend([
            '%m-%d-%Y',

            '%m/%d/%Y',
            '%m/%d/%y',
            '%m/%d/%Y %H:%M:%S',
        ])
    
    for expression in format_expressions:
        try:
            upload_date = datetime.datetime.strptime(date_str, expression).strftime('%Y%m%d')
